{"key":"post-14630151","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>14630151</id>\n<content>Put the cakes anywhere but in the terrarium.&amp;nbsp; If you have to 'drain' the perlite, it means you didn't drill holes on the bottom.&amp;nbsp; You need to clean out the terrarium, empty the perlite and cakes, and then drill 1/4&quot; holes every two inches on all six sides.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Since you used the wrong size cakes, they're probably dry, so you can re-dunk during the process.&amp;nbsp; Boil the perlite and then drop it back in after you're done.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This should have been added to your other thread rather than starting a new one.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14630179</next>\n<prev>14630066</prev>\n<first>14630066</first>\n<last>14637648</last>\n<when>1308363172</when>\n<utime>06/18/11 05:12 AM</utime>\n</post>"}